Subject: Resignation Letter

Dear [Boss's Name],

I hope this email finds you well. I wanted to inform you that I have made the difficult decision to resign from my position at [Company Name], effective [last working day, typically two weeks from the date of the email].

I have thoroughly enjoyed my time working here at [Company Name], and I am grateful for the opportunities and experiences I have gained. The support and guidance I have received from you and the entire team have been invaluable, which has helped me grow both personally and professionally.

However, after careful consideration, I have come to the realization that it is time for me to explore new opportunities and challenges in my career. I believe this transition will allow me to further enhance my skills and knowledge in [mention a specific area that you would like to focus on in your future role].

I assure you that I will fulfill all my responsibilities and ensure a smooth transition during my remaining time here. I will complete any pending projects and ensure that all necessary handovers are completed effectively. Additionally, I am more than willing to assist in the process of finding and training a suitable replacement, should you require my assistance.

I genuinely appreciate the support, trust, and opportunities provided to me during my time at [Company Name